cff-version: 1.2.0
title: HoloWeights
message: >-
  Virtual volumetric tiling and memory-mapped representation for neural network weights,
  with sparse access patterns aimed at inference-time memory bandwidth reduction.
abstract: >-
  Digital virtual holographic weight representation packs model bytes into fixed uint8 tiles,
  persists them as a mmap bank, and routes token-time reads to subsets of tiles. This codebase
  documents mathematics, instrumentation, and conservative claims separately from optics hardware.
authors:
  - name: Mprah-Boamey
type: software
keywords:
  - virtual holography
  - holographic inference
  - volumetric inference
  - optical neural networks
  - optical computing
  - memory-mapped weights
  - sparse tile routing
  - LLM inference
  - quantization
repository-code: https://github.com/mprahboamey/holoweights
license: MIT
